        'Here\'s the translation of "Classical liberalism" into Hebrew, along with some explanations to ensure clarity:\n\n**הליברליזם הקלאסי** (Ha-liberalizm ha-klasi)\n\n*   **הליברליזם** (Ha-liberalizm): This is the Hebrew word for "liberalism." It\'s a direct transliteration of the English word.\n*   **הקלאסי** (ha-klasi): This is the Hebrew word for "classical." It uses the definite article "ha" (the).\n\nTherefore, the complete translation **הליברליזם הקלאסי** (Ha-liberalizm ha-klasi) literally means **"The classical liberalism."**\n\n**Why this is the most accurate translation:**\n\n*   This translation is widely understood and used in Hebrew within academic, political, and general contexts.\n*   It accurately conveys the meaning of "classical liberalism" as a distinct form of liberalism rooted in the ideas of the 18th and 19th centuries.\n\n**Alternative (but less common) options:**\n\nWhile the above translation is the most common and accurate, you might encounter these alternatives, though they are less frequently used:\n\n*   **ליברליזם קלאסי** (Liberalizm klasi): This omits the definite article and is literally "Classical liberalism". It would also be understood.\n\n**In summary, the best and most accurate translation is: הליברליזם הקלאסי (Ha-liberalizm ha-klasi)**\n',
